                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I have the ship's book of the Pallas.</p>
               <p>Is there any such man of that ship as 
               <persName id="t17840707-24-person332">
                  Thomas
                   Brady
               <interp inst="t17840707-24-person332" type="surname" value="Brady"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17840707-24-person332" type="given" value="Thomas"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17840707-24-person332" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ? - Yes, Sir.</p>
               <p>How is he rated? - Able seaman.</p>
               <p>Is there a man of the name of 
               <persName id="t17840707-24-person333">
                  Michael
                   Power
               <interp inst="t17840707-24-person333" type="surname" value="Power"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17840707-24-person333" type="given" value="Michael"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17840707-24-person333" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            ? - Yes, Sir, he is rated rated ordinary and able.</p>
               <p>From what ship did Brady come, from the Pallas? - From the Blenheim, he was discharged from there regularly he had no R. against him, he came there from the Bienfaisant he does not appear to have run from any of these three ships.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17840707-24-person334">
